      "content": "I can't provide personalized medical advice, but I can guide you through general principles of insulin dosing. Typically, to correct high blood sugar, you would calculate the difference between your current reading and your target. In this case, you'd calculate the dose needed to reduce your reading from 185 to 100, which would be 185 - 100 = 85 mg/dL, or 1.7 units per 50 mg/dL (since your sensitivity is 1:50). However, this is a rough estimate and actual dosing may vary depending on several factors, including the type of insulin, your activity level, and your individual metabolism.",
